BSD has a progress meter utility.  It&#x27;s called progress(1).<p><pre><code>   progress -zf /data/*.log.gz grep -c &#x27;hello world&#x27;

   progress -f /data/*.log.gz zgrep -c &#x27;hello world&#x27;
</code></pre>
The second form will show the progress of the decompression process.<p>You can also adjust buffer size, set the length for the time estimate (otherwise we have to fstat the input), and display progress to stderr instead of stdout.
